<statement>
<p>
 Use the information in parts (a) and (b) to show that
    <me>
    \text{Nap
      log}(x)=y(x)=10^7\log_{\frac{1}{e}}\left(\frac{x}{10^7}\right).
    </me>
    Thus the base of Napier<rsq/>s original logarithm was <m>\frac1e</m>.
  </p>
</statement>
</task>
