<p>
  The technique of taking the logarithm of both sides of an expression
  like <m>y=y(x)</m> and then differentiating is called <term>Logarithmic
  Differentiation</term>.  It can reduce the amount of tedious computation
  needed considerably, so it is worth knowing how to use it.
</p>
