<p>
  Finally, we return to <xref ref="EQUATIONDampedProblem1">equation</xref>. In
  <xref ref="PROBLEMDampedOscillator1"></xref> we saw that
  <me> z(t)=e^{-\frac{t}{2}} \left[
  A\cos\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}t\right)+B\sin\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}t\right)
  \right]</me> and  in part (c) of <xref ref="PROBLEMDampOscExpSol"></xref> we saw that
  <me>
    y= e^{-\frac{t}{2}}\left[ae^{\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}it} +
    be^{-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}it}\right]
</me>
is another.
If these are the same solution we can find a
relation between the constants <m>a</m>, <m>b</m>, <m>A</m>, and <m>B</m>.
</p>

